cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper deals with insider threat detection and security challenges within organizations. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the proposed framework utilizes attributed graph clustering techniques for user analysis. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes an outlier ranking mechanism for identifying suspicious users. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the proposed framework involves the analysis of high dimensional, heterogeneous data for insider threat detection. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also relevant as the paper deals with the analysis of network, system and user parameters for identifying suspicious users.
